signatureAbility.signatureDescription: Not all receivers need fancy footwork. When they enter the zone, they have increased success chance on stiff arm and truck attempts following the catch.
Receivers with this ability catch more consistently while catching passes less than 10 yards from the LoS, inside the numbers
Receivers with this ability catch more consistently while catching passes 10-20 yards from the LoS, outside the numbers
Defenders with this ability will frequently attempt and win impact blocks against receivers, tight ends, and running backs.
Defenders with this ability force more catch tackle knockouts in man-to-man versus medium routes, 10-20 yards from the LoS.
Defenders with this ability will frequently prevent additional yardage gains while tackling
Blockers with this ability reduce a rusher's chances of using a quick block shed move.
Blockers with this ability are almost guaranteed to win any double team block they are engaged in
Players with this ability can detect user-controlled defenders before the snap; as well as 3rd and 4th down blitzers. Can be bluffed.
Blockers with this ability will frequently attempt and win pull blocks
When playing from behind, players with this ability can easily enter the Zone.
Passers with this ability improve the catching prowess of all running backs who are open on pass plays.
Passers with this ability improve the catching prowess of all tight ends who are open on pass plays.
Shutdown defenders have the talent to erase receivers from the game. When they enter the zone, their coverage is tighter and interceptions are more frequent on contested catches.
Defenders with this ability generally react much faster to receiver cut moves when in man coverage and outside the numbers
Defenders with this ability force more catch tackle knockouts in man-to-man versus short routes less than 10 yards from LoS
Players with this ability have an increased chance to catch passes that have been tipped into the air.
Defenders with this ability force more catch tackle knockouts in man-to-man versus deep routes 20+ yards from the LoS.
Ballcarriers with this ability have more powerful truck and stiff arm animations and a larger timing window for perfect attempts.
Avoid stumbling when carrying the ball
Ballcarriers with this ability retain more of their forward momentum during tackles while travelling at high speeds.
